---
// About / Meet Jamie section
---

<section id="about" class="px-6 py-24">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
    <!-- Section label -->
    <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-accent">About</p>
    <h2
      class="mb-16 max-w-xl text-3xl font-black text-primary sm:text-4xl"
      style="font-family: var(--font-heading);"
    >
      A trusted partner for 25+ years
    </h2>

    <div class="grid items-center gap-16 lg:grid-cols-2">
      <!-- Left: bio + stat -->
      <div>
        <p class="mb-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
          Booth Accounting is led by Jamie Booth, an experienced accounting professional who has
          spent more than two decades helping clients make sense of their finances. From full-charge
          accounting and financial statements to tax preparation and day-to-day money management, the
          focus is the same: accurate, personal, dependable service — and a real person who knows
          your situation.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-12 text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
          Founded in November 2000, Booth Accounting has built its reputation on long-term client
          relationships and the kind of attentive service that larger firms simply can't offer.
        </p>

        <!-- Trust stat -->
        <div class="flex items-center gap-6 rounded-xl bg-surface p-6">
          <div>
            <p
              class="text-5xl font-black text-accent leading-none"
              style="font-family: var(--font-heading);"
            >
              25+
            </p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-text-muted">
              Years in practice
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="h-12 w-px bg-gray-200" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Serving individuals and small businesses in Huntington Beach, CA since November 2000.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: headshot placeholder -->
      <div class="flex justify-center lg:justify-end">
        <img
          src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}jamie-booth.jpg`}
          alt="Jamie Booth, principal of Booth Accounting"
          width="256"
          height="320"
          class="h-80 w-64 rounded-2xl object-cover object-top"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
